								There are a few differences between these two Un Sdg goals. Life under Water focuses on the life under water and not only on the green house gases but also the amount of plastic waste and toxic chemicals being thrown in the water on a daily basis.The Climate Action Sdg more focuses on the Life on land or the air. Instead of talking about all pollution it talks about greenhouse gases which is only a small amount of all gases. Though these two are some very similar topics that are sourced from similar problems.
							</p>
							
